	â¢	1 packet taco seasoning (or 1 tbsp homemade seasoning)
	â¢	1/4 cup water

	â¢	2 cups shredded cheese (cheddar, Monterey Jack, or a blend)
	â¢	1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed
	â¢	1 cup corn (canned, fresh, or frozen)
	â¢	1/2 cup chopped tomatoes
	â¢	1/4 cup sliced jalapeÃ±os (optional, for heat)

Toppings (Optional):

	â¢	Salsa

	â¢	Hot sauce

Instructions:

	1.	Prepare the Chicken: In a skillet over medium heat, combine the shredded chicken, taco seasoning, and water. Stir until the chicken is evenly coated with the seasoning and the water has absorbed, about 3-5 minutes. Remove from heat.
	2.	Preheat the Oven: Preheat your oven to 400Â°F (200Â°C).
	3.	Assemble the Nachos: On a large baking sheet or oven-safe platter, spread out a layer of tortilla chips. Top with half of the seasoned chicken, black beans, corn, tomatoes, red onion, and shredded cheese. Add another layer of chips and repeat with the remaining ingredients.
	4.	Bake the Nachos: Place the tray in the oven and bake for about 8-10 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.
	5.	Add Fresh Ingredients: Remove the nachos from the oven and sprinkle with fresh cilantro and jalapeÃ±os (if using).
